{"TopicId":198262,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Which field of a camera is changing while scrolling mouse wheel?","CreatedByName":"Xavier513","CreatedById":103114,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-22T04:08:49Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Xavier513","CreatedById":103114,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-22T04:08:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I scroll the mouse wheel in Flight scene, the camera will zoom in or zoom out.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich field in Camera(or FlightCamera) object is changing? How can I zoom in/out with code as if I\u0027m scrolling the wheel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt doesn\u0027t seem to be the \u0022fov\u0022(field of view) field, on the basis of my test results.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:huh:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:huh:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-11-22T04:10:38Z\u0022 title=\u002211/22/2020 04:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 22, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Xavier513\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xavier513","CreatedById":103114,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-24T03:48:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK, it\u0027s \u0022FlightCamera.fetch.Distance\u0022 and \u0022FlightCamera.fetch.SetDistanceImmediate( )\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}